&lt;p&gt;True Anomaly is seeking a skilled and detail-oriented Senior Electrical Analyst to lead worst-case circuit analysis (WCCA) and derating activities across our spacecraft hardware programs. In this role, you will work closely with design engineers and subject matter experts to ensure our electrical systems meet rigorous military and industry standards, from early design through qualification and release. You bring deep analytical expertise, hands-on experience with advanced test and measurement equipment, and the ability to identify and resolve complex electrical issues with precision and clarity. As a senior contributor, you will also mentor junior engineers and drive continuous improvement of our electrical analysis processes and practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct worst-case circuit analysis (WCCA) in compliance with military and industry standards (MIL, ASTM, TIA, EIA, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct derating analysis per EEE-INST-002&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with subject matter expert teams to review findings, update designs as needed, and release WCCA reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and configure test equipment, materials, fixtures, and components to simulate real-world and idealized test conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and analyze complex electronic systems using advanced tools such as oscilloscopes, spectrum analyzers, network analyzers, and time domain reflectometers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately document test and analysis results, including observed defects and corrective actions, in clear and structured reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support root cause analysis and design verification efforts in the context of WCCA and broader system performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with engineering and customer teams to support product development and continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in all aspects of the product development lifecycle, from concept and requirements definition through product release and post-release support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior engineers to improve design skill sets and increase capabilities within the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve electrical engineering processes and practices to drive innovation and efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
